    "These weights are learned to optimize the attention mechanisms and adapt to the specific graph and task.",
    "GATs can be used in multiple layers to capture higher-level features and complex relationships in the graph.",
    "The output of one GAT layer becomes the input for the next layer.The learning weights capture the importance of node relationships and contribute to information aggregation during the neighborhood aggregation process.",
    "The learning process in GNNs also relies on backpropagation and optimization algorithms.",
    "The stacking of GNN layers enables the model to capture higher-level abstractions and dependencies in the graph."
